    Wait, one tiny thing. `parseInt` on a large array of tokens... The `tokens` array is already created by `match`. So `parseInt` will just be called on substrings. This is fine.

    One more check on the constraints: `1 <= C <= 200000`, `1 <= N <= 300000`.
    The number of operations is $N$. The number of tokens is at most $3N+2$.
    The maximum number of `GET` results is $N$.
    The maximum number of keys in the cache is $C$.
    All these are within limits for Node.js memory and time.
